<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-09-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-09-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="582" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d582">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Barrett</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-09-13"><hi rend="italic">September 13,
                                    1904</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 40.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge and
                            confirm telegrams received and sent by this legation.</p>
                        <p>I beg to state that the police of Panama have been notified, and that
                            every possible precaution has been taken by them and by this legation to
                            apprehend the individual in question.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Barrett.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>